A group of multitalented award-winning artists will unite to raise awareness around HIV and Aids in a musical showcase at Carnival City on World Aids Day on December 1. The event will take place at the Big Top Arena in Brakpan and features Afrotraction, Vusi Nova, Ntando and Kabomo, among others. The artists will collaborate in a bid to touch the lives of others and make a difference. They will present an eclectic mix of Afro-soul, neo-soul, Afro-pop and jazz in a show that starts at 7.30pm